frameDefinitions: A Theme, which may or may not have a default shape or configuration, goes into a particular shape without being made to do so by an agent.
The number of entities that make up the Set changes from an Initial_number to a Final_number.
The Payer is (legally) forced to pay a Fine by an official Speaker as a punishment for some action (the Reason).
A Process stops at a certain Time and Place.
This frame contains words which describe the dimensional extent and Shape of a Substance.
An event or state (here termed an Eventuality) or time-Period is described in terms of the Degree to which its duration diverges from a standard.
frameExamples: It <t>curled</t> up into a cylinder after laying in the sun.
How has the <t>proliferation</t> of cellular telephones affected your amateur mobile operation? INI INI
They were <t>fined</t> approximately $3.1 billion dollars for their knowing, malicious injury to consumers.
She held a <t><fex name='Shape'>square</fex></t> of cloth .
After a <t>lengthy</t> discussion with the Foreign Minister, Mr. Qian Qichen, they met the Prime Minister.
listRoleDefinitions: The <fen>Theme</fen> goes into a particular shape.
The <fen>Result</fen> is the shape the <fen>Theme</fen> becomes.
When the changing into a particular shape occurs.
Where the shape-changing event takes place.
The group of entities, possibly construed as a collective, whose number changes.
The number of entities by which the <fen>Set</fen> increases or decreases.
The number of entities in the <fen>Set</fen> afterwards.
The initial number of entities in the <fen>Set</fen>.
A description that presents the <fen>Set</fen>'s state before the change in the number of entities making it up as an independent predication.
A description that presents the <fen>Set</fen>'s state after  the change in the <fen>Attribute</fen>'s value as an independent predication.
The <fen>Time</fen> is the time-frame in which the change in number occurs.
A location where the <fen>Set</fen> changes in number.
The <fen>Speaker</fen> is the person who imposes the <fen>Fine</fen> upon the <fen>Payer</fen>.
The <fen>Payer</fen> is the person or thing about whom/which a judgment is made.  With verbs this role is typically expressed as Object:

Typically, there is a constituent expressing the <t>Reason</t> for the Judge's judgment. It is usually a <ment>for</ment>-PP, e.g. I <t>admire</t> you <fex name='Reason'>for your intellect</fex>. For some words in this domain, the Reason frame element is obligatory. That is to say, the overt expression of this frame element may only be omitted when the reason for the judgment is understood from context. For example, the sentence 'I <t>blame</t> you!' can only be uttered when it is clear what the addressee is being blamed for.
The money given to expiate some debt for transgression.
When the event occurs.
Where the event takes place.
The <fen>Process</fen> which is halting.
When the event occurs.
Where the event takes place.
A <fen>Substance</fen> of which pieces can be extracted.
This is the <fen>Shape</fen> that the <fen>Substance</fen> is in.

A situation, action or event whose duration is being described.  The Eventuality occurs as the External Argument if the adjective is used predicatively, or as the modified noun if the adjective is used attributively: <fex name='Eventuality'>The lecture</fex> was <t>short</t>. We had a <t>lengthy</t> <fex name='Eventuality'>conversation</fex>.

Sometimes these adjectives describe simply a period of time, rather than an event or state.  The Period almost invariably occurs as the modified noun with an attributive adjective: We waited for only a <t>short</t> <fex name='Period'>time</fex>. Use of the drug over a <t>lengthy</t> <fex name='Period'>period</fex> can cause memory loss.
listRoleExamples: <fex>The union's membership</fex> has dwindled from 1.5 million in 1979 to a little more than 600000 today.
Jaffna's student population has dwindled <fex>by more than a hundred</fex>.
Church of England baptisms have dwindled from 365000 in 1940 <fex>to 150000 in 1995</fex>.
The number of Medline searches has greatly proliferated <fex>from 7 million</fex> to 120 million.
The human population has dwindled <fex>from being world dominators</fex> to simple survivors.
Oh, my aching software: Worms and viruses proliferated <fex>in 2003</fex>.
The mental control officer fined <fex>you</fex> for your lack of diligence.
